HEADWORD: Sulphophosphoric
<hw>Sul`pho*phos*phor"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of,
pertaining to, or designating, a hypothetical sulphacid of phosphorus,
analogous to phosphoric acid, and known in its salts.</def>⟦br⟧
